OL,3,CPolitician concerned over Jersey's
OL,4,Cborder authority if UK law introduced
OL,6,FThe legislation would, if introduced,
OL,7,Fgive legal backing to the new
OL,8,FElectronic Travel Authorisation (ETA)
OL,9,Fscheme, and require people from
OL,10,Fcertain countries to obtain an online
OL,11,Fpermit before being able to enter
OL,12,FJersey.
OL,14,FThe border checks are already live
OL,15,Facross the UK and there is pressure on
OL,16,Fthe Crown Dependencies to follow suit
OL,17,Fas they are part of the Common Travel
OL,18,FArea, which currently allows for
OL,19,Fborderless travel between the Channel
OL,20,FIslands and other areas of the British
OL,21,FIsles.
