OL,3,CPolitician concerned over Jersey's
OL,4,Cborder authority if UK law introduced
OL,6,FHowever, the Order in Council, which
OL,7,Fthe Assembly has been asked to
OL,8,Fapprove, includes a clause stating:
OL,9,F"The Secretary of State may, when
OL,10,Frequested to do so by any of the
OL,11,Fislands, carry out functions on behalf
OL,12,Fof that island in relation to the
OL,13,Fauthorisations in electronic form to
OL,14,Ftravel to that island".
OL,16,FSir Bailhache has lodged an amendment
OL,17,Fasking that the clause be removed,
OL,18,Farguing it gives too much power to UK
OL,19,Fofficials over Jersey's affairs.
