OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F385A1757104939
OL,3,CPolitician concerned over Jersey's
OL,4,Cborder authority if UK law introduced
OL,6,FHe says: "It seems to me to go too far
OL,7,F- it delegates to the United Kingdom
OL,8,Fthe right, in effect, to decide who
OL,9,Fcan come to Jersey. That is not
OL,10,Fcorrect.
OL,12,F"It would undermine Jersey's right to
OL,13,Fcontrol its own borders. It would be
OL,14,Fcontrary, I think, to our
OL,15,Fconstitutional arrangements".
OL,17,FSir Bailhache further suggests it
OL,18,Fcould risk island-specific schemes,
OL,19,Fsuch as the one that gives French day
OL,20,Ftrippers access to the islands with
OL,21,Fonly their ID cards.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
