OL,3,CPolitician concerned over Jersey's
OL,4,Cborder authority if UK law introduced
OL,6,FEarlier this year, some British MPs
OL,7,Fraised concerns that this initiative
OL,8,Frisked making Jersey a "backdoor route
OL,9,Finto the UK" for potential illegal
OL,10,Fimmigrants.
OL,12,FSir Bailhache ultimately argues that
OL,13,Fit is important not to undermine
OL,14,FJersey's domestic autonomy, even by
OL,15,Faccident.
OL,17,FHe says: "It does not seem necessary
OL,18,Fto contemplate this delegation of
OL,19,Fpeople to enable the ETA scheme to
OL,20,Fwork smoothly.
